**Privacy Policy for Python School**

**Effective Date:** July 30, 2024

**Introduction**
Welcome to Python School, an educational app designed to help users learn Python programming. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your data when you use our app.

**1. Information Collection**
Python School collects minimal data necessary for providing our services:
- Internet access is required to display educational articles and content
- No personal identification information is collected
- No user data is stored on our servers

**2. Use of the App**
The app requires internet connectivity to:
- Load and display educational articles
- Update content
- Ensure you have access to the latest learning materials

All content access is anonymous, and we do not track individual user behavior or create user profiles.

**3. Data Security**
While our app uses internet connectivity, we ensure:
- All content is accessed through secure connections
- No personal data is transmitted
- No cookies or local storage of personal information is maintained

**4. Children's Privacy**
Python School is safe for use by individuals of all ages, including children under the age of 13. While the app requires internet access, we do not collect any personal information that could identify a child or any other user.

**5. Network Usage**
The app uses internet connectivity solely for:
- Downloading educational articles
- Updating learning materials
- Ensuring content accuracy and relevance

No usage data or personal information is transmitted back to our servers.

**6. Changes to This Privacy Policy**
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and we will update the effective date accordingly. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.

**7. Contact Us**
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our app, please contact us at:

**Email:** bevylabs@gmail.com
